T1  - Anticipated Shocks and Exchange Rate Dynamics
AU  - Wilson, Charles A.
Y1  - 1979/06/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260782
DO  - 10.1086/260782
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 639
EP  - 647
VL  - 87
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - The paper extends Dornbusch's analysis of exchange rate dynamics to include the case where changes in government policy are anticipated before they occur. It is demonstrated that simply the announcement of an expansionary policy will cause the exchange rate to jump, which induces an expansionary impact on the economy even before the policy is implemented.
AB  - The paper extends Dornbusch's analysis of exchange rate dynamics to include the case where changes in government policy are anticipated before they occur. It is demonstrated that simply the announcement of an expansionary policy will cause the exchange rate to jump, which induces an expansionary impact on the economy even before the policy is implemented.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260782
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/260782
Y2  - 2024/03/22
